Package com.cafean.CalcServer.util

Class LegacyCalcJobFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.CalcServer.util.LegacyCalcJobFile
  • public class LegacyCalcJobFile
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper class for a Legacy Calculation Job File (CJF, *.cjf).

    Note: Legacy CJF files start with a token (#!CJF) indicating that it is a valid *.cjf file.

    Note: Plug-in specific properties in the form <plugin-id>:property=value [STRING]

        public boolean isInteractive()

        Note that this property indicates the user's requested interactive status not the current state of the job. If set to true, this property will remain true even after a job has completed, unloaded and reloaded.

      • getFile

        public java.io.File getFile​(java.lang.String key)
        Retrieves the file stored in this CJF with the given key.

        Note: Each file used and/or created by a job must be included in it's CJF as the plug-in may or may not be notified when the job is moved, renamed or removed.

        Parameters:
        key - a String containing the file reference's key. This parameter will be converted to upper case.
        Returns:
        the File requested or null if no file is stored with the given key.

      • getFileKeys

        public java.lang.String[] getFileKeys()
        Returns an array of the keys used to store each file in this CJF. Note that file keys are converted to upper case and prefixed with a token ( usually [{FILE}]_ ) to indicate that they are files rather than normal properties.
        Returns:
        String[] containing the keys used to store each file.

      • getFiles

        public java.io.File[] getFiles()
        Retrieves an array of all of the file references stored in this CJF.
        Returns:
        a File[] containing the on-disk path to the files stored in this CJF obtained by calling getFile() with each of the keys returned by getFileKeys().
